the main view. So the long note becomes something shorter, and I&#8217;m happier.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/i2.wp.com\/nahumck.me\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/10\/Small-Image-Notes.jpeg?w=1100&#038;ssl=1\" style=\"width:75%\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/p>\n<p>One caveat: it&#8217;s applied to all or none. You can either have small or large images. You can&#8217;t apply it to each image, but I&#8217;m hopeful that Apple will include that in the future. For now, I&#8217;m happy that my original frustration yielded this feature discovery.<\/p>\n<ol id=\"footnotes\">\n<li id=\"fn1\">through some epic schemes that I won&#8217;t even begin to describe <a href=\"#ffn1\">&#x21a9;<\/a><\/li>\n<li id=\"fn2\">C&#8217;mon, Apple: how is this not a thing?!? <a href=\"#ffn2\">&#x21a9;<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ol>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>As I was preparing to receive my Apple Watch,1 I started gathering different information that I wanted to refer to when setting it up. I used Notes.app to make saving links a breeze, and I like the way they are saved because they are visually appealing. I also encountered several watch face layouts along the &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/nahumck.me\/a-little-note-on-notes\/\" class=\"more-link\">Continue reading <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">A Little Note on Notes<\/span> <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"spay_email":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_is_tweetstorm":false,"jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true},"categories":[82],"tags":[66],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_publicize_connections":[],"jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p6pMv7-eC","jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":517,"url":"https:\/\/nahumck.me\/using-drafts-as-a-main-text-editor\/","url_meta":{"origin":906,"position":0},"t